) soon. Group of entrepreneurs have resolved to apply to the Department of Electronics and Information Technology (DEITY) to get Vellore region notified as a \u2018Brownfield\u2019 EMC, at a convention held at Kramski office, [[Vellore]] on June, 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Brownfield-electronics-cluster-in-Vellore-soon/2013/06/15/article1635097.ece#.UveehNL7C8A|title=Brownfield electronics cluster in Vellore soon|date= 15 June 2013|work=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/first-move-towards-electronic-cluster-in-vellore-district/article4816691.ece|title=First move towards electronic cluster in Vellore |date= 15 June 2013|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> On 18 January 2014 'Brownfield' Electronics Cluster in [[Vellore]] region has been approved.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/brown-field-electronics-cluster-approved/article5589265.ece|title=Brown Field Electronics Cluster approved |date= 18 January 2014|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n\n=== IT SEZ ===\nAs per the policy directive of Government of Tamil Nadu, ELCOT is promoting Information Technology Parks in Tier I and in the Tier II cities. Integrated Information Technology Campusus consisting of Information Technology buildings as well as Residential and Social Infrastructure facilities will be established with Government and Public Private Partnership (PPP) mode in Vellore along with other Tier II Cities.<ref name=ECTN>{{cite web|title=IT Specific SEZ in Tier II Cities|url=http://www.elcot.in/sezs_main.php|publisher=Electronics Corporation of Tamil Nadu Limited (ELCOT) |accessdate=2013-07-07}}</ref> Chief Minister [[Jayalalithaa]] announced in December 2012 that feasibility study of IT park in Vellore will be initiated.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/article1388057.ece#.Uvig2NL7C8A|title=Jayalilathaa revives IT park plan in Vellore |date= 21 Dec 2012|work=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n\n== Industries ==\n\n=== Leather industries ===\n\nAs leather industries in this region, contribute a major share in country's leather export there are several major leather factories few among them are,\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#ffd722;\"| Company\n! style=\"background:gold;\" ! | Year & Founder\n!! style=\"background:gold;\"| Plants/Factories\n!! style=\"background:gold;\"| Employment\n|-\n|FARIDA Group<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.farida.co.in/faridagroup.php|title=About Farida Group|publisher=Farida Group|accessdate=2014-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140316104611/http://www.farida.co.in/faridagroup.php|archive-date=16 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|1957 by Haji Mecca Abdul Majid Sahib\n|12\n|7000+\n|-\n|KH Group<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khshoes.net/Aboutus.aspx|title=About KH Group|publisher=KH Group|accessdate=2014-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140209091159/http://khshoes.net/Aboutus.aspx|archive-date=9 February 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|1982 by Khizar Hussain\n|4\n|7000\n|-\n|TAW\n|1949 by T. Abdul Wahid & Co\n|3\n|3400\n|-\n|NMZ\n|1972 by N M Zackriah\n|5\n|1800\n|-\n|-\n|Florence<ref>{{cite web |url=http://business.highbeam.com/665/article-1G1-100047009/italian-standardmade-india-florence-shoe-company-have |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222024204/http://business.highbeam.com/665/article-1G1-100047009/italian-standardmade-india-florence-shoe-company-have |url-status=dead |archive-date=2014-02-22 |title=About Florence Shoes|publisher=High beam Business|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref>\n|1979 by Aqueel Ahmed\n|10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_FLORENCE.html |title=Members Directory - Florence Shoes|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref>\n|NA\n|-\n|}\n\nOther major factories are Althaf Shoes,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_ALTHAF.html |title=Members Directory - Althaf Shoes|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref> Bachi Shoes,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_BACHI.html |title=Members Directory - Bachi Shoes|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref> Florind Shoes, IRBAZ Group,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_IRBAZ.html |title=Members Directory - IRBAZ Group of Companies|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref> TMAR Group,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_TM.html |title=Members Directory - TMAR & Sons|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref> Nibras Shoes and SSC.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indianshoefederation.in/members/mem_shoe_SSC.html |title=Members Directory - SSC Shoes|publisher=Indian Shoe Federation|accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Automobile industries ===\nAutomobile and mechanical companies of global Brands, including [[SAME Deutz-Fahr]], TVS\u2013Brakes India, [[Mitsubishi]], [[Greaves Cotton]] and MRF have their manufacturing units in the area.\n[[File:Trattori Same.jpg|thumb|Right|[[SAME Deutz-Fahr]] tractors]]\n*'''SAME Deutz-Fahr India''', part of the [[SAME Deutz-Fahr]] group of [[Italy]] has their plant at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]]. Manufacturers of tractors, engines and agricultural machinery firm entered [[India]] in 2005 with initial investment of 88 Crores. It exports tractors in the range of 35-70 HP and components - engines and transmission. Production capacity was 6,300 tractors per annum in the year 2009. In the year 2008, the company exported 1,500 units to the US and Europe and has set a target to double the figure in the coming year. This facility will cater to markets like Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and African countries.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/same-deutz-fahr-to-make-ranipet-its-export-hub-109030500059_1.html|title=SAME Deutz-Fahr to make Ranipet, Vellore its export hub |date=5 March 2009|work=[[Business Standard]]}}</ref> SAME Deutz-Fahr (SDF) India Group planning to introduce the premium brand [[Lamborghini]] tractors in India. The group is also planning to make India its global production hub for engines within the next three years and will move its global tractor engine production from Italy and Germany to the plant of its Indian arm, Same Deutz-Fahr India at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2013-04-21/news/38710201_1_engines-tractors-ranipet|title=Lamborghini tractors to soon roar in Indian fields |date=21 April 2013|work=[[The Economic Times]]}}</ref> [[SAME Deutz-Fahr]] is planning to expand its production base in this plant. The plan is to get to 30-35 HP at the lower end and 80-100 HP at the upper range. Currently the production capacity of this plant is 15,000 tractors per year and its planning to increase it further.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sdf-to-widen-tractor-range-offering-in-india-to-hike-capacity-113042200257_1.html|title=SDF to widen tractor range offering in India,to hike capacity |date=8 Feb 2014|work=[[Business Standard]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-business/same-deutzfahr-group-to-expand-india-facility/article324166.ece|title=\nSame Deutz-Fahr group to expand India facility|date= 5 March 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n*'''[[Greaves Cotton]]''' part of [[Thapar Group]] manufacturers of  [[automotive engine]] (diesel and petrol engines for three- and four-wheelers), construction equipments gensets and farm equipments has their manufacturing unit at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]]. [[Greaves Cotton]] plans to expand its construction equipment products range. This 1,700-crore multi-product company, has signed a pact with Samil of South Korea seeking technical know-how for products such as stationary concrete pumps and boom pumps. The company is also planning to expand its diesel engine manufacturing capacity at this plant.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/article3377281.ece|title=Greaves Cotton mulls expansion of construction equipment products |date=2 May 2012|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n*'''Bavina Cars''' India Limited, has been allotted a 100-acre plot at [[Ranipet]] SIPCOT's SEZ for its hybrid electric car manufacturing facility at an investment of 300 crores<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/ranipet-sez-to-host-bavina-cars/article226373.ece|title=SIPCOT\u2019s SEZ at Ranipet will play host to Bavina Cars India |date=11 July 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> with a capacity to produce 40,000 cars per year with technology support from Velozzi of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.in/bline/2009/07/14/stories/2009071451400200.htm|title=Bavina Cars India investing 300 crores at Ranipet SIPCOT's SEZ |date=14 July 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> This will be the second battery-powered car production unit in the country after Bangalore\u2019s Reva Electric Car.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/business/india-to-get-second-electric-car-plant-by-2011_100216323.html|title=India to get second electric car plant|date=7 Oct 2009|work=Thai Indian}}</ref> There are reports that this project has been on hold due to financial issues of the firm.\n\n=== Engineering & manufacturing industries ===\n[[File:BHEL logo.svg|100px|thumb|BHEL]]\n*'''[[Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited]] (BHEL)'''  is an Indian state-owned integrated power plant equipment manufacturing company. Its Boiler Auxiliaries Plant (BAP) is located at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]]. [[BHEL]] [[Ranipet]] has performed exceedingly well according to its executive director as it has won the \u2018Best Productive Unit\u2019 trophy from among all the units of [[BHEL]] for the year 2012. This plant has clocked a turnover of 4,210 crore with shop production crossing the 1 lakh metric tonne benchmark and also registered a profit before tax of 1,260 crore for the 2012 financial year. It has so far obtained 21 patents and 46 copyrights.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/bhel-ranipet-is-best-productive-unit/246253-60.html|title= BHEL Ranipet is best productive unit|date=7 April 2012|work=[[IBN Live]]}}</ref>\n\n:[[BHEL]]-Boiler Auxiliaries Plant, [[Ranipet]] is installing a 5 MW solar power plant which will cover the entire energy needs of the plant <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Solar-Plant-in-BHEL-to-be-Commissioned-in-2-Months/2014/01/28/article2023965.ece#.UvjrYtL7C8A|title= Solar Plant in BHEL|date=28 January 2014|work=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref> and it also has entered into a technology tie-up with [[Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]], [[Japan]], to manufacture and supply flue gas desulphurisation system meant for removal of sulphur dioxide from flue gases.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/bhel-ranipet-unit-in-tech-tie-up-with-mitsubishi-113041200600_1.html|title= BHEL-Ranipet unit in tech tie-up with Mitsubishi|date=12 April 2013|work=[[Business Standard]]}}</ref>\n\n[[File:ArcelorMittal.svg|180px|thumb|ArcelorMittal]]\n*'''[[ArcelorMittal]] Dhamm Processing Private Limited''' is a joint venture firm between the world's largest steel producing firm [[ArcelorMittal]] and [[Mumbai]] based Dhamm Steel for manufacturing steel components at an estimated cost of 100-crores at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]]. It manufactures finished steel components for earth moving equipment manufacturers, construction and power industries.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.steelguru.com/indian_news/ArcelorMittal_and_Dhamm_Steel_form_steel_unit_JV_in_Vellore/64255.html|title= ArcelorMittal and Dhamm Steel form steel unit JV in Vellore|date=25 Sep 2008|work=Steel Guru}}</ref>\n*'''[[MRF Limited]] (Madras Rubber Factory limited)''' is an India-based company engaged in manufacturing, distribution and sale of tyres for various kinds of vehicles ranging from helicopters to automobiles is located at [[Arakkonam]], [[Vellore]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.in/2009/05/30/stories/2009053050840300.htm|title=MRF unit to reach full capacity soon|date=30 May 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n\n=== Precision tool industries ===\n[[File:MHI logo.jpg|150px|thumb|Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]]\n*'''Mitsubishi Heavy Industries India Precision Tools Limited (MHI-IPT)''', a subsidiary of [[Japan]]-based [[Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]], opened its plant at [[Ranipet]], [[Vellore]] in 2007, doubling its production capacity in gear cutting tools.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.oneindia.in/2007/08/09/mitsubishi-opens-new-plant-in-ranipet-1186668188.htmlt|title=Mitsubishi opens news Plant in Ranipet, Vellore|date=9 August 2007|work=[[Oneindia.in]]}}{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Products manufactured by MHI-IPT at this plant are Hobs, Shaping cutters, Gear Shaving cutters, Master Gears, Broaches and Rotary cutter.\n*'''KRAMSKI Stamping and Molding''' India Pvt Ltd, a subsidiary of '''KRAMSKI GmbH''' headquartered in [[Pforzheim]], [[Germany]], precision metal and plastic integrated-component manufacturing company with automotive, telecommunications, electronics and medical applications is located on a 10-acre site at Erayankadu, about 16&nbsp;km from the [[Vellore]] city on the Chennai-Bangalore National Highway, established at the cost of Rs.15 crore which is the lone Indian plant of this Germany based firm.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/23/stories/2009022353100300.htm|title= German company\u2019s first Indian subsidiary coming up near Vellore|date=23 Feb 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KRAMSKI India, Vellore Plant|url= http://www.kramski.de/en/meta-navigation/kontakt-indien.html}}</ref> KRAMSKI, which has currently located its office in the [[Vellore Institute of Technology]]-Technology Business Incubator (VIT-TBI), has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the VIT-TBI for soft launching of the company in [[Vellore]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/german-multinational-firm-to-set-up-plant-near-vellore/article1341638.ece|title= German multinational firm to set up plant near Vellore|date=20 Sep 2008|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> This plant being one among the two plants in [[Asia]] from KRAMSKI GmbH was inaugurated by [[Vellore]] Collector in the year 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/german-company-unit-inaugurated-in-vellore/article222308.ece|title= German company unit inaugurated in Vellore|date=7 July 2009|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n\n:KRAMSKI Stamping and Molding India Pvt Ltd a leading manufacturer of electronic components has won two ELCINA-EFY (Electronic Industries Association of India-Electronics For You) awards. One award for being the Outstanding Electronics SME (Small and Medium Enterprise) of the Year Special Jury Award for its achievements by an Electronics SME in India in the medium company category for the year 2012\u201313, and the second prize in Excellence in Environment Management under the SME category (for a medium company) another award for the same year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/vellorebased-firm-bags-two-elcina-awards/article5166406.ece|title= Vellore-based firm bags two ELCINA awards|date=25 Sep 2013|work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref>\n\n*'''TVS-Brakes India''' Sholingur's foundry division is located at [[Vellore]]-[[Sholingur]] to manufacture Permanent Mould Grey Iron castings with an installed capacity of 5,000 MTPA which later increased to 26,000 MTPA in the year 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brakes India Foundry Division Official Website|url= http://www.brakesindia.com/brakesfoundry/index.html|publisher=Brakes India Limited|accessdate=2013-07-07}}</ref>\n\n=== Explosives industries ===\n*'''[[Tamil Nadu Industrial Explosives Limited]] (TNIE)''' is Asia's biggest explosives manufacturing company, located at [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]]. This is India's only government explosives company. The company is headed by a senior [[Indian Administrative Service]] officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tniel.net/inner.php?pagesv=contact|title=Welcome to TNIEL|publisher=TNIEL|accessdate=2013-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611000734/http://www.tniel.net/inner.php?pagesv=contact|archive-date=11 June 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Service sector industries ===\nVellore is among the top medical destination in the country due to the presence of [[Christian Medical College & Hospital]] (CMCH), which ranks top in the country. CMCH is located on [[Ida S. Scudder|Ida Scudder]] Road in the heart of the city, and its Vellore's largest private employer and has a large floating population from other parts of India and abroad. The [[Government Vellore Medical College]] and Hospital (VMCH) is located at Adukamparai in [[Vellore]]. With the advent of hospitals such as [[Apollo KH Hospital]] in Melvisharam and [[Sri Narayani Hospital & Research Centre]] in Sripuram medical tourism is rapidly growing.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Vellore]]\n[[Category:Economy of Tamil Nadu|Vellore]]\n[[Category:Economies by city in India|Vellore]]\n", "name_user": "Samaniran", "label": "safe", "comment": "Copy editing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economy_of_Vellore"}
